==English==

===Etymology===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*lewh₃-}}
First attested in the early 15th Century. From {{inh|en|enm|absolven}}, from {{bor|en|la|absolvere}}, present active infinitive of {{m|la|absolvō||set free, acquit}}, from {{m|la|ab||away from}} + {{m|la|solvō||loosen, free, release}}. {{doublet|en|assoil}}.

